workers, and customers.ConsShort staffing which results in stressed employees who are underpaid. Benefits are not great.Advice to ManagementPay employees more and care more about employees. Give better training like in the past.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (1) First South Bancorp (NC) Response seconds agoEdit • Delete First South Bancorp (NC) 2016-05-09 16:05 PDT Join the First South Bancorp (NC) team See Our Latest Jobs Jun 8, 2016 Helpful (2)"Branch Operations Manager"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementFormer Employee - Branch Operations ManagerFormer Employee - Branch Operations ManagerDoesn't RecommendNegative OutlookApproves of CEOProsLending - offers a lot more product offerings than most banks that set our bank apartGreat CEO - Bruce Elder was very kind and seemed to truly care about his teammates!Cons- The pay was far below that of other banks. Tellers normally start at just $10 per hour. Many Branch Managers make in the $35,000-40,000 range. Market Presidents only make in the $80,000 range so honestly there isn't a lot of money to be had. In addition, the bonuses inside the branch aren't even worth discussing. You are looking at $50-100 per month as potential earnings and the goals aren't realistic at all to achieve.- The company states You First - however, there isn't hardly any sign of actually putting the customer first. For example, the customer service hours are regular business hours. Many customers let us have it in the branch on Monday mornings due to an issue they had with our bank (we had a lot of problems with our online banking since it wasn't very good) on Monday mornings. They really don't live out the You First slogan well.- Many upper management are very poor leaders and short sighted. The new retail banking director was full of himself and too pompous to provide any coaching to (not a 360 degree person at all). His lack of leadership led to the retail banking leaders following his lead which led to a lot of problems to the branch teams below. Also, God forbid you make a mistake. The upper management will pile on you with full force as if they never made a mistake before. It's ridiculous, talk about walking on egg shells.- The bank was infested with gossip and back stabbing. A lot of it arose from the retail banking director and retail banking leaders. My team and I were actually lied to on two occasions and we verified from within. It was something that the upper management thought we actually didn't talk amongst one another inside the branches. The morale was low as a result and was and made it easy for me to look out and find another job to get out of this sinking ship.Advice to Management- Have you management teams treat others as they would want to be treated! Show respect, act humbly, have the heart of a servant and be kind! There was so much backstabbing, deceit and gossip around the bank at the time I left. I was so thankful to be able to leave the bank when another opportunity arrived.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) First South Bancorp (NC) Response seconds agoEdit • Delete First South Bancorp (NC) 2016-06-08 15:55 PDT Apr 17, 2015 Helpful (1)"Commercial loan officer"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeDoesn't RecommendNegative OutlookNo opinion of CEOI have been working at First South Bancorp (NC) full-timeProsNot many. Nice employees. City exec was good.ConsSmall minded leaders, conflicting information, good ole boy network, no training, poor communication of company's strategy. I could go on and on but my advice is look somewhere else.Advice to ManagementLearn what customer service is. Develop a consistent strategy that the employees can support. Invest in your staff.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (1) First South Bancorp (NC) Response seconds agoEdit • Delete First South Bancorp (NC) 2015-04-17 05:37 PDT Aug 23, 2014"Credit Analyst"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementFormer Employee - Credit Analyst in Washington, NCFormer Employee - Credit Analyst in Washington, NCRecommendsNeutral OutlookNo opinion of CEOI worked at First South Bancorp (NC) full-time (Less than a year)ProsThe people were nice and friendly. It was easy to get alone with others. Everyone was willing to talk and communicate.ConsLow pay, which should be higher. There are better opportunities at other banks in the area.Advice to ManagementIncrease pay.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) First South Bancorp (NC) Response seconds agoEdit • Delete First South Bancorp (NC) 2014-08-23 10:27 PDT Nov 15, 2010"Good, but could be better"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementFormer Employee - Retail Sales Associate & Loan Administrative AssistantFormer Employee - Retail Sales Associate &amp; Loan Administrative AssistantApproves of CEOProsgreat co-workers, laid back branch, standard banking productsCons"jump in and figure it out" is something that happens a lot. You can call the same department with the same question and get a different answer for each person you ask. There really needs to be standard training for all positions.Advice to ManagementListen to employees, make opportunities available to employees regarding trainingShare on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHe